1 1. Examine the financial status of the Teachers' Retirement System medical
2 insurance fund;
3 2. Assess the long-term sustainability of the shared responsibility solution;
4 3. Receive input from a diverse group of stakeholders, including representatives
5 from education organizations and the retirement systems; and
6 4. Explore potential policy changes and recommendations to the General
7 Assembly upon the medical insurance fund achieving full actuarial funding, including but
8 not limited to adjustments to contribution requirements, long-term funding policies, and
9 the overall financial structure of the plan.
10 Section 2. The Shared Responsibility Solution Task Force shall be composed of
11 the following members, with final membership of the task force being subject to the
12 consideration and approval of the Legislative Research Commission:
13 (1) Three members of the House of Representatives appointed by the Speaker of
14 the House of Representatives, one of whom shall be designated by the Speaker of the
15 House of Representatives as a co-chair of the task force;
16 (2) Three members of the Senate appointed by the President of the Senate, one of
17 whom shall be designated by the President of the Senate as a co-chair of the task force;
18 (3) One member of the House of Representatives appointed by the Minority Floor
19 Leader of the House; and
20 (4) One member of the Senate appointed by the Minority Floor Leader of the
21 Senate.
22 Section 3. The Shared Responsibility Solution Task Force shall meet at least
23 monthly during the 2025 Interim of the General Assembly. The task force shall submit
24 findings and recommendations to the Legislative Research Commission for referral to the
25 appropriate committee or subcommittee thereof by December 1, 2025.
26 Section 4. Provisions of this Resolution to the contrary notwithstanding, the
27 Legislative Research Commission shall have the authority to alternatively assign the
